@Phantom\_of\_the\_FNM  
Ever heard of something called the Reserve List?  

@Shadoflaam  
Go up against one, you'll find it's still an incredibly viable black card even today. Not only is it very powerful but it hits the board turn 1 with [Dark Ritual](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Dark Ritual)s. Sure, [Phyrexian Obliterator](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Phyrexian Obliterator) will do that for you just fine, but this works better in 2-color decks, not just monoblack. It might be expensive, but that's a.) it's age and b.) the fact that when you play it, you get your money's worth out of it. So the Obliterator's better, how do you make up for it? Run both in monoblack Legacy. This card too expensive for you to buy? Try its cheaper cousin, [Grinning Demon](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Grinning Demon). Worried about the life loss? Learn to play the game.  

I got into the game too late to truly enjoy this card, but I still appreciate and respect both its history and its power. 5/5

